Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a self-interference cancellation scheme for full-duplex orthogonal frequency division multiplexing systems, which involves estimation and cancellation phases. This involves the use of minimum mean square error estimator, which is a common technique in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed scheme is relevant to networking and internet architecture as it aims to improve the performance of full-duplex systems by suppressing self-interference caused by oscillator phase noise. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper focuses on improving the performance of full-duplex communication systems by suppressing self-interference caused by oscillator phase noise. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed scheme involves the use of estimation and cancellation phases, which are common techniques in systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed scheme is relevant to multimedia applications as it aims to improve the performance of full-duplex systems, which are commonly used for multimedia communication.
